The paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques to improve the performance of low-dose X-ray CT reconstruction. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and residual learning also suggests the possibility of machine learning (cs.LG) being a relevant sub-category. The paper also mentions the estimation of noise in the input wavelet transform, which could be related to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the use of X-ray CT images suggests that multimedia (cs.MM) could also be a relevant sub-category.
